19 WHEREAS, one hundred fifty (150) years ago, in October 1875, two
20 hundred twenty-five (225) Arkansas physicians formed what is now the Arkansas
21 Medical Society; and
22
23 WHEREAS, from the inception of the Arkansas Medical Society, the
24 physician members of the Arkansas Medical Society have made it their mission
25 to advance the art and science of medicine and improve the health and well-
26 being of the citizens of the State of Arkansas; and
27
28 WHEREAS, over the past one hundred fifty (150) years, the physicians of
29 the Arkansas Medical Society have been instrumental in addressing the health
30 needs of our state, and the monumental efforts of these physicians, while
31 often obscured by the passage of time, deserve our lasting appreciation; and
32
33 WHEREAS, the efforts of the physicians of the Arkansas Medical Society
34 include:
35 (1) The creation of the state's first State Board of Health in
36 1879;
